1
00:00:03,666 --> 00:00:05,666
أعوذ بِٱللَّهِ مِنَ ٱلشَّيْطَـٰنِ ٱلرَّجِيمِ

2
00:00:09,189 --> 00:00:11,189
Bism Allah Arrahman Arraheem

3
00:00:11,189 --> 00:00:13,484
In the name of God, Most Gracious, Most Merciful.

4
00:00:17,246 --> 00:00:22,010
Dr. Khalifa: This morning about 9 o'clock, Lisa asked me "do you know that you're giving the Khutba?

5
00:00:23,264 --> 00:00:26,188
It was quite a surprise as you realize.

6
00:00:26,427 --> 00:00:31,904
Then after the Khutbah, Lydia came to me and
said "do you know you're giving the Quranic study?"

7
00:00:32,904 --> 00:00:34,951
And she took the beating on behalf of Lisa.

8
00:00:34,951 --> 00:00:37,681
Actually, Lisa sent her to tell me that.

9
00:00:39,890 --> 00:00:41,260
So, here I am.

10
00:00:41,809 --> 00:00:44,059
First of all, we welcome a new member to our
masjid.

11
00:00:45,731 --> 00:00:46,709
This person here.

12
00:00:48,500 --> 00:00:49,901
I forgot his name.

13
00:00:54,201 --> 00:00:57,767
This is the former, and still is, Muhtesem
Erisen, the one and only.

14
00:00:58,185 --> 00:00:59,140
Mã Shã Allãh

15
00:00:59,140 --> 00:01:00,252
Welcome back.

16
00:01:04,074 --> 00:01:09,502
Before I start, there is also one more point
that I wanted to mention.

17
00:01:09,502 --> 00:01:11,536
Thanks to our Iranian brothers and sisters.

18
00:01:12,253 --> 00:01:16,870
There is a little bit of confusion now about
your arms, what to do with your arms when you pray.

19
00:01:17,467 --> 00:01:19,588
Keep them like this and put them straight
down.

20
00:01:20,304 --> 00:01:25,425
I would like to establish first, once and
for all, that it doesn't make any difference,

21
00:01:25,425 --> 00:01:28,048
whether you go like this or put your hands
down.

22
00:01:28,884 --> 00:01:33,734
But generally, what I do is I follow what
the Imam is doing.

23
00:01:34,331 --> 00:01:38,136
The person in the front, whatever the person
in front is doing, I do what he's doing.

24
00:01:38,673 --> 00:01:42,488
And I recommend that for you.

25
00:01:47,385 --> 00:01:50,864
IN SHAA ALLAH, we'll be doing Sura 90, The Town.

26
00:01:52,416 --> 00:01:54,391
And whatever we can afterwards.

27
00:01:55,107 --> 00:01:58,739
At 8:30, the children will practice on us.

28
00:01:59,337 --> 00:02:01,158
You know, they'll be singing at the conference.

29
00:02:01,755 --> 00:02:06,349
So, we'll give them maybe 20 minutes, 20 minutes to 9.

30
00:02:06,632 --> 00:02:07,632
20 minutes enough?

31
00:02:07,991 --> 00:02:10,364
20 minutes to practice a new song on us.

32
00:02:12,514 --> 00:02:14,469
It should be enjoyable, IN SHAA ALLAH.

33
00:02:17,694 --> 00:02:19,948
Sura 90, The Town.

34
00:02:20,366 --> 00:02:22,717
In the name of God, Most Gracious, Most Merciful.

35
00:02:23,911 --> 00:02:26,209
[90:1]  I solemnly swear by this town.

36
00:02:27,463 --> 00:02:29,431
[90:2]  The town where you live.

37
00:02:31,580 --> 00:02:33,239
[90:3]  The begetting and the begotten.

38
00:02:34,194 --> 00:02:38,659
[90:4]  We created the human being to work hard (to redeem himself).*

39
00:02:39,853 --> 00:02:42,863
[90:5]  Does he think that no one will ever call him to account?

40
00:02:43,400 --> 00:02:46,510
[90:6]  He boasts, "I spent so much money!"

41
00:02:46,809 --> 00:02:48,857
[90:7]  Does he think that no one sees him?

42
00:02:50,111 --> 00:02:52,063
[90:8]  Did we not give him two eyes?

43
00:02:53,436 --> 00:02:55,116
[90:9]  A tongue and two lips?

44
00:02:55,534 --> 00:02:56,677
Number 10,

45
00:02:56,677 --> 00:02:58,677
[90:10]  Did we not show him the two paths?

46
00:03:00,140 --> 00:03:02,030
[90:11]  He should choose the difficult path.

47
00:03:02,866 --> 00:03:05,087
[90:12]  Which one is the difficult path?

48
00:03:06,520 --> 00:03:08,550
[90:13]  The freeing of slaves.

49
00:03:09,148 --> 00:03:11,293
[90:14]  Feeding, during the time of hardship.

50
00:03:11,890 --> 00:03:13,530
[90:15]  Orphans who are related.

51
00:03:13,530 --> 00:03:15,324
[90:16]  Or the poor who is in need.

52
00:03:15,981 --> 00:03:23,733
[90:17]  And being one of those who believe, and exhorting one another to be steadfast, and exhorting one another to be kind.

53
00:03:24,323 --> 00:03:26,114
[90:18]  These have deserved happiness.

54
00:03:26,473 --> 00:03:30,793
[90:19]  As for those who disbelieved in our revelations, they have incurred misery.

55
00:03:31,347 --> 00:03:34,148
[90:20]  They will be confined in the Hellfire.

56
00:03:35,342 --> 00:03:36,928
So, that's the whole Sura.

57
00:03:38,242 --> 00:03:40,177
I go back to the beginning, swearing.

58
00:03:40,177 --> 00:03:47,882
God usually starts many of these short Suras
with a profound statement.

59
00:03:48,717 --> 00:03:51,365
And this town, meaning Mecca, is profound.

60
00:03:51,365 --> 00:03:56,579
Because God made it sacred by putting His
shrine there

61
00:03:56,579 --> 00:03:59,209
to serve as the focal point.

62
00:03:59,209 --> 00:04:02,788
or a point of organization for all believers
around the world.

63
00:04:02,788 --> 00:04:08,269
When we stand in Prayer, we don't fight as
to which direction we should face.

64
00:04:08,807 --> 00:04:12,990
God already decided for us that we're gonna face the direction of Mecca.

65
00:04:13,587 --> 00:04:20,845
So, every believer, every Muslim around the
world is praying and facing that point.

66
00:04:22,457 --> 00:04:26,946
So, the first verse is simply a profound statement,
as in many other Suras.

67
00:04:28,075 --> 00:04:31,658
And it is the town where the Prophet Muhammad
lived

68
00:04:31,658 --> 00:04:33,582
from whom this Quran was revealed.

69
00:04:35,560 --> 00:04:39,193
"The begetting and the begotten" is a profound
statement again.

70
00:04:39,637 --> 00:04:44,787
All these profound statements precede an important
proclamation.

71
00:04:45,407 --> 00:04:54,511
The begetting and the begotten, this is a
profound fact of life.

72
00:04:54,511 --> 00:04:56,281
Take for example birds.

73
00:04:57,430 --> 00:04:58,746
The bird laying an egg.

74
00:04:59,516 --> 00:05:03,624
The egg has been fertilized by two parents,
through two parents.

75
00:05:04,613 --> 00:05:08,766
One half, a reproductive cell is half a normal
cell.

76
00:05:09,274 --> 00:05:15,000
One reproductive cell from the male and one
half, the other half comes from the female.

77
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:17,050
They combine to form an embryo.

78
00:05:17,668 --> 00:05:21,830
In birds, the egg is laid, it is fertilized.

79
00:05:21,830 --> 00:05:32,390
And then, the fact that the birds sit on the eggs,
you know they take turns, the male and female in most species.

80
00:05:32,917 --> 00:05:34,726
Taking turns sitting on the egg.

81
00:05:35,263 --> 00:05:36,591
Why do they do that?

82
00:05:37,128 --> 00:05:38,761
Who taught them to do that?

83
00:05:39,478 --> 00:05:42,136
And what's happening inside that shell, the
egg?

84
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:56,120
After a period of time, that it is becoming obvious
more and more that it's a multiple of 7. 21 days in some birds.

85
00:05:56,730 --> 00:05:58,626
21, 7 times 3.

86
00:05:59,163 --> 00:06:04,062
The human fetus now is in the mother's womb
266 days.

87
00:06:04,062 --> 00:06:08,794
It is now established scientifically. 266, not 265.

88
00:06:09,045 --> 00:06:12,292
266 and that's 19 times 2 times 7.

89
00:06:12,292 --> 00:06:14,281
That's still a multiple of 7.

90
00:06:18,522 --> 00:06:20,952
Gestation period, is it called the gestation
period?

91
00:06:22,086 --> 00:06:23,926
Is that the period inside the womb?

92
00:06:24,225 --> 00:06:30,000
Ok. In many other species, I know it is a multiple
of 7, but I'm being distracted now.

93
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:33,824
However, "the begetting and the begotten" is
a profound statement.

94
00:06:35,684 --> 00:06:41,884
After 21 days, the bird inside breaks through
the shell and comes out.

95
00:06:43,138 --> 00:06:47,829
Then, they're walking around. If they're ducks, they go in the water and they swim. You know, as if they've been here forever.

96
00:06:48,643 --> 00:06:49,773
As if they know everything.

97
00:06:49,773 --> 00:06:53,122
Walking around, following their mother in the
water.

98
00:06:54,628 --> 00:06:58,263
You can go to a random spot and see them. They just came out of the egg.

99
00:06:59,215 --> 00:07:05,031
And they're full of wisdom, you know, just following the mother wherever she goes. And sometimes they go independently and pick at something in the water.

100
00:07:06,731 --> 00:07:09,651
And they're identical to their parents.

101
00:07:11,320 --> 00:07:14,320
With beaks and eyes. Where did this come from?

102
00:07:15,566 --> 00:07:20,053
And you can do this with any kind of species,
any begetting and begotten.

103
00:07:22,056 --> 00:07:25,333
Now here comes the proclamation. Number 4.

104
00:07:25,333 --> 00:07:29,065
[90:4]  We created the human being to work hard (to redeem himself).*

105
00:07:31,065 --> 00:07:36,110
As a result of that crime that we committed
millions of years ago,

106
00:07:36,110 --> 00:07:40,200
where we did not make a firm stand with God's
absolute authority,

107
00:07:40,200 --> 00:07:42,200
we are here.

108
00:07:43,812 --> 00:07:50,948
And God designed our plan to work hard, to
redeem ourselves, to denounce that crime,

109
00:07:50,948 --> 00:07:56,830
to prove that we are on the side of God's
absolute authority.

110
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:02,717
What do you call getting up in the morning
before sunrise?

111
00:08:03,493 --> 00:08:07,643
It's not easy, is it? At the beginning, especially when our soul
is still small and weak.

112
00:08:08,598 --> 00:08:11,912
The soul cannot wake up the body initially.

113
00:08:12,808 --> 00:08:14,390
Because the soul is weak.

114
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:16,403
It is hard work.

115
00:08:18,135 --> 00:08:23,300
And you are rewarded by growth, nutrition,
and strength of the soul.

116
00:08:28,794 --> 00:08:30,794
[90:4]  We created the human being to work hard.....

117
00:08:32,466 --> 00:08:38,049
The lazy person who does not work hard and
does not get up before sunrise, what is the result?

118
00:08:39,493 --> 00:08:47,745
He or she ends up with a shrunken, weak soul
that will not amount to anything in the real life, the Eternity.

119
00:08:50,080 --> 00:08:53,132
They will be born into Eternity deformed.

120
00:08:56,237 --> 00:09:01,163
And we see this in Sura 68 where they cannot
fall prostrate.

121
00:09:01,778 --> 00:09:06,332
On that big day when God comes physically
to our universe,

122
00:09:06,332 --> 00:09:08,380
they will not be able to, they have no legs.

123
00:09:08,380 --> 00:09:11,097
I mean, this is symbolically. They are deformed.

124
00:09:11,694 --> 00:09:14,172
A stump cannot fall prostrate.

125
00:09:15,683 --> 00:09:17,096
They are deformed.

126
00:09:17,574 --> 00:09:19,156
It is lack of growth.

127
00:09:20,990 --> 00:09:25,257
To get up in the morning before sunrise and
do the Morning Prayer is a gift from God.

128
00:09:25,795 --> 00:09:31,090
If we deserve it, God will guide us into waking
up before sunrise to do the Morning Prayer.

129
00:09:34,434 --> 00:09:41,265
For the young people, I don't want you to
be alarmed because it may be difficult for you, but eventually

130
00:09:41,265 --> 00:09:45,479
you will be able to train
your body to get up in the morning before sunrise.

131
00:09:46,180 --> 00:09:48,740
If you are unable to do it now, don't be too
disturbed.

132
00:09:51,009 --> 00:09:54,600
It is normal. Let me tell you this because
I don't wanna be too hard on you.

133
00:09:54,845 --> 00:09:58,102
It is normal to start out by doing one prayer
a day.

134
00:09:59,017 --> 00:10:03,122
Let us say the Morning Prayer as soon as you
get up at 10 or 11 in the morning.

135
00:10:04,475 --> 00:10:06,810
Then, it will be two prayers a day.

136
00:10:07,885 --> 00:10:09,811
Then, it will be three prayers a day.

137
00:10:10,661 --> 00:10:14,207
Then, you will do the Morning Prayer before
sunrise and you will enjoy it.

138
00:10:16,588 --> 00:10:23,080
The ideal situation is to do the five Prayers
with the Morning Prayer done before sunrise.

139
00:10:24,812 --> 00:10:29,676
Also, God tells us in the Quran that we cannot
do it every day. You're gonna miss once in a while.

140
00:10:31,169 --> 00:10:36,453
So, always think of the positive and be glad,
be happy with the achievements that you do.

141
00:10:37,408 --> 00:10:41,199
If you miss one time a week or something,
don't feel too guilty.

142
00:10:42,393 --> 00:10:47,677
Be glad that you did six out of the seven
days, Morning Prayers before sunrise.

143
00:10:48,334 --> 00:10:53,499
Ideally, you will not miss anything. You will do the Morning before sunrise and you will do the other four Prayers as well.

144
00:10:54,036 --> 00:10:58,186
[90:4]  We created the human being to work hard (to redeem himself).*

145
00:10:59,559 --> 00:11:04,545
There's a footnote here that says "see the
Introduction and Appendix 7 for the purpose behind our creation.

146
00:11:05,770 --> 00:11:07,069
Redeem ourselves.

147
00:11:07,666 --> 00:11:09,960
Go back to God's kingdom where we were.

148
00:11:10,676 --> 00:11:20,138
We got ourselves out by being interested in
Satan's theory that others besides God can have power.

149
00:11:22,213 --> 00:11:24,521
And the people are doing the same mistake
now.

150
00:11:24,999 --> 00:11:32,442
They think Jesus can have power, or Mary, or Saint Jude, or Muhammad, or Ali, or Hussein, or Mahdi, or whatever.

151
00:11:33,846 --> 00:11:35,853
People are repeating the same mistake.

152
00:11:36,510 --> 00:11:38,962
We did. God saved us.

153
00:11:39,499 --> 00:11:41,224
This is how we get redeemed.

154
00:11:42,478 --> 00:11:47,770
By upholding the words of God alone and worshipping
God alone.

155
00:11:50,397 --> 00:11:53,701
Number five talks about those who fail to
redeem themselves.

156
00:11:54,180 --> 00:11:57,073
[90:5]  Does he think that no one will ever call him to account?

157
00:11:58,186 --> 00:12:06,845
See, everything we do here is credited to
us or held against us, whatever we do here.

158
00:12:09,377 --> 00:12:15,963
And anything is forgivable except idol worship

159
00:12:15,963 --> 00:12:17,645
if maintained until death.

160
00:12:20,576 --> 00:12:23,619
That's the unforgivable crime, because this
is why we are here.

161
00:12:24,030 --> 00:12:30,000
We are here for just one reason, to establish
the fact that we know that only God possesses all power.

162
00:12:31,746 --> 00:12:37,346
And so number five is telling us that every
one of us will be called to account.

163
00:12:39,081 --> 00:12:43,006
With the majority of people, they'll be asked "why didn't you develop your soul?

164
00:12:43,006 --> 00:12:48,789
How come you fed your body three meals a day,
but you failed to feed yourself, your soul?"

165
00:12:51,538 --> 00:12:57,858
Most people go through their whole life without
feeding the real person a single meal.

166
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:02,159
This is repeated in the Quran.

167
00:13:02,580 --> 00:13:05,195
Most people, no matter what you do, will not
believe.

168
00:13:05,676 --> 00:13:11,537
And most of those who believe will fall into
idolatry, into idol worship.

169
00:13:12,087 --> 00:13:14,078
And we see this everywhere, don't we?

170
00:13:15,678 --> 00:13:21,393
Just think of any mosque in the world that
says the Adhan, for example, the call to prayer, devoted to God alone,

171
00:13:21,393 --> 00:13:25,483
without the name of Muhammad or Ali or somebody
besides God.

172
00:13:28,060 --> 00:13:33,577
In all of Iran or Pakistan or Egypt or Saudi
Arabia, there isn't a single one mosque

173
00:13:33,577 --> 00:13:37,350
that is devoted to God alone, which goes against the commandments of the Quran.

174
00:13:39,511 --> 00:13:41,193
What happened to their brains?

175
00:13:42,626 --> 00:13:46,171
They're just repeating what they did in the
High Society.

176
00:13:52,083 --> 00:13:55,813
[90:5]  Does he think that no one will ever call him to account?

177
00:13:56,291 --> 00:13:58,530
[90:6]  He boasts, "I spent so much money!"

178
00:13:58,530 --> 00:14:00,344
Isn't this what most people do?

179
00:14:02,812 --> 00:14:05,109
They're preoccupied with the almighty dollar.

180
00:14:10,424 --> 00:14:14,133
In the meeting with our brothers and sisters
in New York, I was asking them

181
00:14:14,133 --> 00:14:18,080
"when you get up in the morning, what is your list of priorities?"

182
00:14:19,937 --> 00:14:22,329
"Are you going to have three meals today?"

183
00:14:24,960 --> 00:14:28,274
Just when you open your eyes in the morning,
ask yourself these questions.

184
00:14:28,274 --> 00:14:30,858
"What am I gonna do today? I'm gonna have three meals today?"

185
00:14:31,591 --> 00:14:34,431
That's about 30 minutes, at least.

186
00:14:35,001 --> 00:14:36,709
"Am I going to the bathroom today?"

187
00:14:37,180 --> 00:14:38,426
Two or three times.

188
00:14:40,248 --> 00:14:42,037
"Am I going to work today?"

189
00:14:43,112 --> 00:14:44,637
Four to eight hours.

190
00:14:45,577 --> 00:14:48,040
"Am I going to exercise today?"

191
00:14:48,432 --> 00:14:50,059
Thirty to sixty minutes.

192
00:14:50,856 --> 00:14:54,251
"What else will I do? Will I watch the TV today for one or two hours?"

193
00:14:56,109 --> 00:15:00,737
"Will I give God twenty-five minutes? Will I do my five Prayers today?"

194
00:15:02,917 --> 00:15:08,163
Even with some Muslims, the five Prayers take
a back seat to everything else.

195
00:15:09,358 --> 00:15:11,793
You ask them "why don't you come to the Friday
prayer?"

196
00:15:12,931 --> 00:15:15,000
"Why don't you do the five Prayers?"

197
00:15:15,590 --> 00:15:20,720
They will say "I had an appointment here and there, and I
did this and that, and there was no time for the Prayer."

198
00:15:25,487 --> 00:15:31,823
But we thank God because all of us here, we work
our schedules around the Prayers, the five Prayers.

199
00:15:31,823 --> 00:15:33,767
That's the proper thing to do.

200
00:15:35,125 --> 00:15:40,374
It should be that when we get up in the morning,
on top of the list will be the five Prayers, at least.

201
00:15:42,644 --> 00:15:43,644
On top of the list.

202
00:15:44,045 --> 00:15:47,011
Then, if there is time for anything else, we
will do that.

203
00:15:48,863 --> 00:15:53,906
This is why the verse that says "most of those
who believe, fall in idol worship."

204
00:15:54,462 --> 00:15:58,437
Because when you give priority to anything
else, that's your idol.

205
00:15:59,109 --> 00:16:04,027
Now, don't get me wrong. There are situations
where you are forced by circumstances to miss

206
00:16:04,027 --> 00:16:08,285
a Prayer or two, or a Friday, an occasional
Friday.

207
00:16:08,676 --> 00:16:10,696
And I don't want you to feel guilty about
that either.

208
00:16:10,980 --> 00:16:16,243
Because God Himself in the Quran gives you,
knows what's in your heart, and gives you excuses.

209
00:16:16,721 --> 00:16:21,766
But generally in your life, you're giving
priority to God and your duties towards God,

210
00:16:21,766 --> 00:16:24,184
which are actually a gift from God to you.

211
00:16:25,199 --> 00:16:28,990
So, when you get up in the morning, you think,
I'm gonna have three meals today.

212
00:16:29,571 --> 00:16:34,927
I'm gonna give my body at least a half
hour for eating.

213
00:16:34,927 --> 00:16:37,225
Eating, drinking, snacking, more.

214
00:16:38,002 --> 00:16:39,673
You're really taking care of your body.

215
00:16:40,986 --> 00:16:42,139
How about your soul?

216
00:16:43,990 --> 00:16:47,352
The believers have their priorities in the
right order.

217
00:16:48,725 --> 00:16:53,473
When I open up my eyes in the morning, the
five Prayers, this will take precedence over everything else.

218
00:16:59,233 --> 00:17:00,000
Number six,

219
00:17:00,000 --> 00:17:02,000
[90:6]  He boasts, "I spent so much money!"

